00:01:40,660 --> 00:01:44,200
[A Moment But Forever]

2
00:01:45,050 --> 00:01:47,140
[Episode 23]

3
00:01:51,479 --> 00:01:52,350
Come with me.

4
00:01:56,039 --> 00:01:56,789
-Snitching, huh?
-Snitching, huh?

5
00:01:56,789 --> 00:01:57,840
-How dare you!
-How dare you!

6
00:01:57,840 --> 00:01:58,509
Stop!

7
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:05,950
I want him.

8
00:02:46,670 --> 00:02:47,640
[Master Yan's Mansion]

9
00:03:01,550 --> 00:03:02,830
This isn't right.

10
00:03:02,310 --> 00:03:04,650
[Master Yan of the human race, Guan Zhi]

11
00:03:04,300 --> 00:03:06,180
Not right. Not right.

12
00:03:07,030 --> 00:03:08,080
Something's off.

13
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:09,120
What's not right?

14
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:11,750
Master.

15
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:13,080
You came at the right time.

16
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:14,190
Take a look at this drawing.

17
00:03:14,430 --> 00:03:15,400
Master.

18
00:03:15,630 --> 00:03:16,520
The servants told me

19
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:17,360
that you haven't had

20
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:18,870
a proper meal in days.

21
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:20,710
Can't you eat first

22
00:03:20,710 --> 00:03:21,630
before working on the drawing?

23
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:23,079
I can't even finish the drawing.

24
00:03:23,079 --> 00:03:24,560
How can I have the mood to eat?

25
00:03:25,079 --> 00:03:26,150
Come on, take a look.

26
00:03:39,030 --> 00:03:40,079
I've always said

27
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:42,340
you're suited for learning craftsmanship.

28
00:03:42,590 --> 00:03:44,470
But you insist on taking over your father's position.

29
00:03:44,620 --> 00:03:45,970
What a waste of talent.

30
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:48,030
There are thousands of craftsmen in Yandu City,

31
00:03:48,150 --> 00:03:50,190
and you have students all over the world, Master.

32
00:03:50,190 --> 00:03:51,520
You won't miss just one like me.

33
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:52,590
But I'm my father's

34
00:03:52,590 --> 00:03:54,430
only son.

35
00:03:55,520 --> 00:03:56,310
Your father has obtained

36
00:03:56,310 --> 00:03:57,960
the immortal pill from the Youhu Clan.

37
00:03:58,110 --> 00:03:59,710
After he comes out of seclusion this time,

38
00:03:59,870 --> 00:04:01,590
he'll have several decades of good life ahead.

39
00:04:01,870 --> 00:04:03,240
Between you two,

40
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:05,400
it's hard to say who will die first.

41
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:06,910
You don't need to rush to take over.

42
00:04:07,560 --> 00:04:08,870
Master, your words...

43
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:11,050
Are absolutely right.

44
00:04:11,910 --> 00:04:12,840
Of course, my father will

45
00:04:12,840 --> 00:04:14,030
live a long life.

46
00:04:14,150 --> 00:04:16,430
You too, Master.

47
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:17,680
I'm not that blessed.

48
00:04:18,950 --> 00:04:20,750
I don't know if I'll ever have the chance

49
00:04:21,040 --> 00:04:22,310
in this lifetime

50
00:04:22,310 --> 00:04:24,800
to have a read of the Wushuang Secret Manual.

51
00:04:24,870 --> 00:04:26,600
Master, you're still looking for the Wushuang Secret Manual?

52
00:04:27,430 --> 00:04:28,950
Isn't that just a rumor?

53
00:04:29,390 --> 00:04:30,950
If that rumor is false,

54
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:33,680
then these questions in my mind

55
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:36,950
might never be resolved in this lifetime.

56
00:04:41,010 --> 00:04:41,930
Oh, by the way, Master.

57
00:04:42,430 --> 00:04:43,240
Has Shen Ying

58
00:04:43,630 --> 00:04:45,310
been here recently?

59
00:04:46,510 --> 00:04:48,270
He hasn't been here for quite some time.

60
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:53,040
He's also your disciple.

61
00:04:53,159 --> 00:04:54,750
He used to serve you diligently

62
00:04:54,750 --> 00:04:55,870
and was very respectful.

63
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:59,170
I suppose he must have been too busy lately.

64
00:05:00,390 --> 00:05:01,190
Why?

65
00:05:01,750 --> 00:05:02,920
Did he offend you?

66
00:05:03,630 --> 00:05:05,360
No, Master, you're being too serious.

67
00:05:05,480 --> 00:05:06,680
He brought Dai

68
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:08,000
and the immortal pill back.

69
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:10,000
It's fair to say his achievements are outstanding.

70
00:05:10,190 --> 00:05:11,750
Father has entrusted him with important responsibilities.

71
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:13,040
Recently, in the city,

72
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:14,870
he's also taken on the role of the Imperial Guard Commander.

73
00:05:14,930 --> 00:05:16,050
He's been very busy.

74
00:05:17,070 --> 00:05:18,680
Everyone's busy with their own affairs.

75
00:05:19,190 --> 00:05:20,000
That's good.

76
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:24,040
What's in that box you brought?

77
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:26,290
So mysterious.

78
00:05:26,750 --> 00:05:28,480
If I didn't ask, you wouldn't take it out, would you?

79
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:30,430
On my way here, I passed by Qiju Pavilion

80
00:05:30,430 --> 00:05:31,360
and found it interesting.

81
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:32,120
So I bought it.

82
00:05:33,580 --> 00:05:34,230
Master.

83
00:05:46,150 --> 00:05:48,710
Thriving and prosperous, making money hand over fist.

84
00:05:50,510 --> 00:05:51,820
Exquisite.

85
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:53,480
Master.

86
00:05:53,820 --> 00:05:55,070
Even in a random utensil shop,

87
00:05:55,070 --> 00:05:56,650
we can find such craftsmanship.

88
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:57,800
It shows that

89
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,830
our race is full of talented individuals.

90
00:05:59,860 --> 00:06:01,470
There's great potential in craftsmanship.

91
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:03,510
Master.

92
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:06,040
As long as we work together with one heart and mind,

93
00:06:06,270 --> 00:06:07,480
given time,

94
00:06:07,510 --> 00:06:09,800
why should we worry about the human race not thriving?

95
00:06:10,250 --> 00:06:11,890
Exquisite.

96
00:06:14,750 --> 00:06:15,870
Truly exquisite.

97
00:06:27,370 --> 00:06:29,060
This is the house I've rented.

98
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:30,800
Come on in.

99
00:06:32,659 --> 00:06:34,560
How is it? Not bad, right?

100
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:36,680
It's really spacious.

101
00:06:37,750 --> 00:06:39,360
There are several rooms here.

102
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:40,610
This one here is where I live.

103
00:06:40,630 --> 00:06:42,040
Those two are empty.

104
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:43,240
I was thinking of renting them out,

105
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:44,240
and you came.

106
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:45,270
Isn't that a coincidence?

107
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:47,720
They can all be cleaned up later.

108
00:06:53,390 --> 00:06:54,190
Look.

109
00:06:54,510 --> 00:06:55,510
How's this room?

110
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:00,680
You can stay in this room.

111
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:04,830
I just moved in not long ago,

112
00:07:04,830 --> 00:07:05,950
and I only cleaned up the main room.

113
00:07:05,950 --> 00:07:07,720
This room can be lived in after a quick clean.

114
00:07:08,110 --> 00:07:09,800
The owners of this place are surnamed Liu.

115
00:07:10,050 --> 00:07:11,490
They're also well acquainted with my family.

116
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:13,800
Their entire family moved away recently,

117
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:15,310
so this house became vacant.

118
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:16,600
Knowing I wanted to rent a place,

119
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:17,950
they rented it to me at a good price.

120
00:07:21,190 --> 00:07:22,240
This side room

121
00:07:22,240 --> 00:07:23,070
used to be

122
00:07:23,070 --> 00:07:23,960
where their second daughter lived.

123
00:07:23,980 --> 00:07:25,660
She liked to arrange flowers and plants.

124
00:07:26,190 --> 00:07:27,240
Those in the courtyard

125
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:29,040
were also planted by that Miss Liu before.

126
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:30,800
So this was a young lady's boudoir.

127
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:36,000
Sir.

128
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:39,040
Just stay here comfortably and recover.

129
00:07:39,330 --> 00:07:40,530
You're Tanyin's friend,

130
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:41,680
which makes you my friend too.

131
00:07:42,310 --> 00:07:43,480
In one's lifetime,

132
00:07:43,630 --> 00:07:44,390
everyone has difficult times

133
00:07:44,390 --> 00:07:45,430
when the path ahead seems narrow.

134
00:07:45,430 --> 00:07:47,070
Hold your breath and endure it.

135
00:07:47,159 --> 00:07:49,120
With a broad mind, the world becomes broad.

136
00:07:51,070 --> 00:07:52,270
Thank you, Xue.

137
00:07:52,390 --> 00:07:54,190
We'll pay you the rent.

138
00:07:56,190 --> 00:07:57,000
Alright.

139
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:58,310
If I don't let you pay,

140
00:07:58,310 --> 00:07:59,720
you probably won't feel comfortable staying here.

141
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:00,600
Don't worry.

142
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:02,240
I'll definitely take good care of him.

143
00:08:02,630 --> 00:08:03,900
I'll go make some delicious food.

144
00:08:04,010 --> 00:08:05,330
Have dinner here, alright?

145
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:11,680
You wait here for a moment.

146
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:12,830
I'll go tidy up a bit.

147
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:22,950
You've finished cleaning?

148
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,270
Do you need my help?

149
00:08:24,270 --> 00:08:25,830
No need, you rest.

150
00:08:25,830 --> 00:08:26,950
Just relax and wait for dinner.

151
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:29,480
Tanyin,

152
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:30,950
who is he?

153
00:08:31,360 --> 00:08:32,870
He's kind of a friend of mine.

154
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:33,640
His name is Qian Lin.

155
00:08:33,659 --> 00:08:34,630
Qian Lin?

156
00:08:34,960 --> 00:08:36,390
That's quite a nice name.

157
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:38,270
I noticed he doesn't talk much.

158
00:08:38,270 --> 00:08:39,789
He wasn't like this before.

159
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:41,150
Don't worry.

160
00:08:41,150 --> 00:08:42,480
I'll take good care of him.

161
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:43,960
He probably won't stay for long.

162
00:08:44,030 --> 00:08:45,490
I'll make time to come over every day.

163
00:08:45,750 --> 00:08:47,550
Xue, sorry for the trouble.

164
00:08:48,270 --> 00:08:49,420
There's no trouble at all.

165
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:12,550
Xue bought a set of old clothes

166
00:09:12,550 --> 00:09:13,720
from the neighbor next door.

167
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:15,030
You can change into them later.

168
00:09:22,240 --> 00:09:23,030
Qian Lin.

169
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:24,670
We've come to know each other.

170
00:09:24,750 --> 00:09:25,840
Since I met you,

171
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:27,320
I won't turn a blind eye.

172
00:09:27,390 --> 00:09:28,240
If you're willing,

173
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:29,390
you can stay.

174
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:31,550
If you don't want to and wish to leave,

175
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:32,550
you're also free to do so.

176
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:37,750
Get some rest first.

177
00:09:38,390 --> 00:09:39,910
You're letting me stay just like this?

178
00:09:42,510 --> 00:09:43,550
I am a War Demon.

179
00:09:45,270 --> 00:09:46,480
So what if you're a War Demon?

180
00:09:47,100 --> 00:09:48,610
War Demons are people too.

181
00:10:13,550 --> 00:10:15,360
Take care, you two. Please come again.

182
00:10:15,360 --> 00:10:16,000
Okay.

183
00:10:18,880 --> 00:10:19,670
Sir,

184
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:21,320
are you waiting for someone?

185
00:10:23,270 --> 00:10:25,000
You must be waiting for your wife, right?

186
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:30,790
You're truly blessed, Sir.

187
00:10:30,790 --> 00:10:31,720
Your wife

188
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:33,480
is both gentle and virtuous.

189
00:10:33,480 --> 00:10:35,000
She leaves early and returns late every day.

190
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:37,120
I heard she works at Qiju Pavilion

191
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:38,510
as a craftsman, right?

192
00:10:39,390 --> 00:10:40,580
That's impressive. Truly impressive.

193
00:10:40,670 --> 00:10:42,080
This is really enviable.

194
00:10:45,420 --> 00:10:46,420
Oh, by the way, Sir,

195
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:48,000
it's raining outside.

196
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,390
Did you bring an umbrella?

197
00:11:11,980 --> 00:11:13,270
♫Listening♫

198
00:11:13,290 --> 00:11:16,790
♫Toona leaves knock fireflies into a vase♫

199
00:11:16,810 --> 00:11:19,780
♫Ripples faintly spreading♫

200
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:22,040
♫In the pavilion in the clouds♫

201
00:11:22,070 --> 00:11:24,030
♫Warm wine brews to the sound of the zither♫

202
00:11:24,230 --> 00:11:28,690
♫The fragrance lingers like brush strokes, sketching out your form♫

203
00:11:29,420 --> 00:11:30,580
♫Tonight♫

204
00:11:30,740 --> 00:11:34,600
♫In a light intoxication, I feel the longing in the crystalline snow♫

205
00:11:34,620 --> 00:11:37,470
♫I cannot bear to think of you♫

206
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:37,750
Yuanzhong!

207
00:11:37,860 --> 00:11:39,500
♫I only wish♫

208
00:11:39,520 --> 00:11:41,350
♫That the years would remain ever sunny♫

209
00:11:39,870 --> 00:11:40,600
What's this?

210
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:42,480
It's a treasure basin. I just bought it.

211
00:11:41,760 --> 00:11:45,930
♫So that, within the drifting light, I could share the breeze with you♫

212
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:45,960
Are you here to pick me up?

213
00:11:46,480 --> 00:11:47,360
Where's Xiu?

214
00:11:46,540 --> 00:11:47,510
♫The wind blows♫

215
00:11:47,360 --> 00:11:48,200
At the noodle shop.

216
00:11:47,530 --> 00:11:48,930
♫It stirs the scenery♫

217
00:11:48,360 --> 00:11:49,910
You left him there alone?

218
00:11:49,140 --> 00:11:50,680
♫It awakens our heart♫

219
00:11:49,910 --> 00:11:51,120
Aren't you worried he might get lost?

220
00:11:50,700 --> 00:11:54,350
♫It makes me certain that you are my destiny♫

221
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:52,240
You wish.

222
00:11:52,320 --> 00:11:53,200
Who would steal him?

223
00:11:54,980 --> 00:11:56,220
♫The closer we get♫

224
00:11:55,630 --> 00:11:56,440
Let's go.

225
00:11:56,240 --> 00:11:57,850
♫The more it feels like a dream♫

226
00:11:57,870 --> 00:11:59,240
♫And the more I look intoxicated♫

227
00:11:59,270 --> 00:12:03,590
♫I cannot fully express my yearning for you♫

228
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:04,720
♫The wind blows♫

229
00:12:04,740 --> 00:12:06,500
♫It blows away the shadows of the clouds♫

230
00:12:06,540 --> 00:12:08,200
♫It makes the moon seem even brighter♫

231
00:12:08,220 --> 00:12:12,400
♫It makes me wake up from a dream♫

232
00:12:12,420 --> 00:12:13,650
♫The wind blows♫

233
00:12:13,680 --> 00:12:15,270
♫It reddens my eyes♫

234
00:12:15,300 --> 00:12:17,300
♫It warms the promise we made♫

235
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:20,930
♫In the wind, we gently♫

236
00:12:20,960 --> 00:12:23,640
♫Drift into a better place♫

237
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:34,870
Young lady, you're back.

238
00:12:35,340 --> 00:12:36,980
Thank you for looking after Xiu for us.

239
00:12:38,550 --> 00:12:39,910
So the little one is called Xiu?

240
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:41,090
He looks sturdy and strong.

241
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:42,150
Quite adorable.

242
00:12:42,480 --> 00:12:43,100
Oh, by the way,

243
00:12:43,270 --> 00:12:45,000
are you two having noodles today as well?

244
00:12:45,870 --> 00:12:46,510
Yes.

245
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:47,260
Alright then.

246
00:12:51,390 --> 00:12:52,750
I got paid today.

247
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:53,840
Although I spent some,

248
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:55,030
there's still quite a bit left.

249
00:12:55,140 --> 00:12:55,860
I went and

250
00:12:55,890 --> 00:12:57,130
exchanged it for gold beans.

251
00:13:02,230 --> 00:13:03,060
Today, Xiu

252
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:04,660
can finally eat a bit more.

253
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:09,030
You go sit down first.

254
00:13:09,290 --> 00:13:10,090
I'll go wash my hands.

255
00:13:10,530 --> 00:13:11,090
Okay.

256
00:13:47,220 --> 00:13:48,220
Your noodles are here.

257
00:13:48,240 --> 00:13:48,970
Thank you.

258
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:50,910
What's wrong with him?

259
00:13:51,790 --> 00:13:53,120
He ate the gold beans but didn't get full,

260
00:13:53,190 --> 00:13:54,190
and now he's throwing a tantrum.

261
00:13:55,030 --> 00:13:56,510
Do we really not need to go look for him?

262
00:13:56,670 --> 00:13:57,370
It's alright.

263
00:13:57,480 --> 00:13:58,120
After he's done with his tantrum,

264
00:13:58,120 --> 00:13:59,150
he'll be back soon.

265
00:13:59,170 --> 00:13:59,960
Let's eat the noodles.

266
00:14:07,890 --> 00:14:08,570
Tell me,

267
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:10,170
why doesn't he grow no matter how much he eats?

268
00:14:12,270 --> 00:14:13,720
Why do you want him to grow up?

269
00:14:16,870 --> 00:14:17,840
Why, you ask?

270
00:14:18,510 --> 00:14:19,270
Aren't we staying here

271
00:14:19,270 --> 00:14:21,030
in order to raise him?

272
00:14:25,750 --> 00:14:26,670
What's wrong?

273
00:14:27,480 --> 00:14:28,270
Nothing.

274
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:32,630
I guess I'm still not earning enough.

275
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:34,320
If children don't eat well,

276
00:14:34,500 --> 00:14:35,740
their health will suffer.

277
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:37,630
He's a weapon spirit,

278
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:38,960
not a child.

279
00:14:45,870 --> 00:14:46,670
Yuanzhong.

280
00:14:47,790 --> 00:14:48,600
Yuanzhong!

281
00:14:49,270 --> 00:14:50,840
Yuanzhong! Yuan-

